The Nigeria Customs Service, Murtala Muhammed International Airport Command, has intercepted $8,065,615 at the airport. Hameed Ali, the customs comptroller-general, said at a press conference in Lagos Tuesday that the cash was intercepted in a car while it was about to be loaded into an aircraft. He did not provide details of the aircraft but added that the money was stashed inside a vehicle belonging to the Nigerian Aviation Handling Company (NAHCO) Mr. Ali said a suspect, the driver of the vehicle and a staff of NAHCO, had been arrested in connection with the alleged money laundering. He said the money was wrapped in large brown envelopes with the names of would-be owners. “From the day we seized this money, no bank has come to claim ownership. But our investigation will reveal the mystery behind the owners,” Ali said. Credit: Premium Times